CASE Statements: The Swiss Army Knife of SQL
Case is a serious SUPER POWER in SQL because it can help you categorize data, replace nulls, create binary columns, and even PIVOT data in SQL. Yes, like making a pivot table summarize your data! We don’t have time to learn alllll of this here, but head on over to my 🔗intermediate course [ https://substack.com/redirect/95908cbc-1f01-4c28-adb0-4c619a88f116?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ] if you want to learn more on CASE and become an expert 😉 CASE is one the biggest ROI SQL skills you can learn, so my intermediate course has a WHOLE chapter on them.
Case works like a fancy if then statement where you can define multiple conditions and it will output the result for the first condition met. Here’s the basic syntax:
case 
   when condition1 then output1
   when condition2 then output2
   ...
   when conditionN then outputN
   end as column_name
Because it steps through the conditions in order, ORDER MATTERS if your logic is dependent on the previous conditions. That means if you’re relying on waterfall logic and depending on and building off of the previous conditions above, you have to make sure your logic is super tight and there are no holes or unaccounted for edge cases. It’s really easy to accidentally forget an equals sign or mess up your numbers and produce incorrect results. See the query below where we rely on waterfall logic to classify revenue.
select 
    order_id,
    price * quantity as rev,
    case 
        when rev < 100 then ‘small’
        when rev < 500 then ‘med’
        when rev < 1000 then ‘large’ 
        else ‘extra large’
    end as rev_amount
from 
    orders
;
If the first condition isn’t true, we go to the second. If the second condition isn’t true, we go to the third. And so on until a condition is true! For example, the second condition (classifying med) relies on the logic that the number is less than 500, and assumes it’s also greater than or equal to 100 since the first condition was NOT met. And for the 3rd condition (classifying large) relies on the logic that the number is less than 1000, and assumes it’s also greater than or equal to 500 since the first and second conditions were NOT met. This is what I mean by waterfall logic!
To emphasize my point further, see what happens when you switch the order of the conditions and put large on top. Does this change your output? It does, because it’s no longer relying on the small and medium conditions since they’re further down in the logic and CASE returns the FIRST met condition output. This produces INCORRECT results below and accidentally misclassifies all the small and medium values as LARGE:
select 
    order_id,
    price * quantity as rev,
    case
        when rev < 1000 then ‘large’ 
        when rev < 100 then ‘small’
        when rev < 500 then ‘med’ 
        else ‘extra large’
    end as rev_amount
from 
    orders
; 
This is why order matters when you use dependent waterfall logic and why you have to be so careful when defining logic in CASE. If you want to write a query that does not rely on waterfall logic (and order doesn’t matter), you can clearly define the upper and lower endpoints of your value ranges. Just be careful with your equal signs here and don’t leave any holes in your logic. See the YouTube video 🔗 [ https://substack.com/redirect/45aa62ad-a79c-4b48-988c-a5f9311d89aa?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ] for an example of this!

column7: A free membership webinar, a feedback request, and the pros and cons of video
column9:
Hi there, 
 There are a lot of great things happening in the Podia community these days! If you haven’t stopped by in a while, you might be missing out on conversions, learning opportunities, and insights like these: 
 - Podia Pro Brittany Hardy is hosting a free webinar about building the Marketing Club membership, including what worked, what flopped, and what moved the needle in her business. Event details and a signup link are in her post. 
- Andy Ziegler from the Business Navigator shared their Podia website and is asking for feedback. Take a look and share your suggestions in the comments. 
- And Estevan Carlos Benson kicked off this discussion of video content vs written content, which has gotten several thoughtful replies. Click through to share what you’ve learned from your experiences. 
 Community access is included free on all plans, so start your 30-day free trial today to join the conversation and make new creator friends! 
 



 
 [Image "Podia+Blogging+Blog+Post+Announcement+Images.png?expires=1759300074&signature=47affdc1f0a8659f5fd1bf391e7251219c763b58639b913de9e8b17c43d3dc23&req=dSUlEs19lIVbUfMW2XS%2FiejohRA%2BpC8QXmwAZdUOtBFgfqDNhKQ%3D%0A"] 
 



 
 See you in the community, 
 Spencer from Podia

View this post on the web at https://jessramosdata.substack.com/p/exposing-all-my-data-salaries

Got BDE?⚡️
Hi data baddies 💅🏼
Subscribe on YouTube 🎥 [ https://substack.com/redirect/e8f6f0e7-107a-428d-bcf0-015e67721e38?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ]— Just hit 12K subs 🎉
And BIG announcement… I’m planning some big, BIG Black Friday deals including a NEW COURSE! Make sure to add your name to the waitlist so you find out FIRST when the deals all launch. Spots are limited so get on the list!!
I over-doubled my salary in an 11-month period.
I increased my salary by 110% in only 11 months!!! 🥵
How’d I do it?
Salary transparency matters, so I’ll share all of my past roles and my biggest negotiation tips.
KEY:
🪩 means that I negotiated my salary
🚀 means that I moved companies
(of course I gave y’all a key… I mean I’m a data expert😉)
Here are all of my past roles:
Server: $5/hour
Graduate Assistant: $17/hour + tuition waved
Data Analyst Intern: $17/hour 🚀
Data Analyst: $71,500 + $19K bonuses
Senior Data Analyst: $73K
Data Analytics Manager: $95K 🪩
Senior Risk Analyst: $130 + $9K bonus 🪩🚀
Senior Data Analyst: $153K 🪩🚀
Job Hopping and Cashing in 🤑
For my first Data Analytics role, I didn’t negotiate my salary much because I didn’t think I was worth it. (don’t follow in my footsteps here, PLEASE negotiate even if it’s your first role! Companies expect you to, and if you don’t you’re leaving money on the table!!)
Then I was later promoted in title a year later but I didn’t receive a salary increase. I tried and they said no. They didn’t have a lot of budget, and I didn’t come as prepared as I should’ve been… UNTIL…
When I was promoted again to Data Analytics Manager, I advocated for a salary adjustment (+29%) since I was managing people, planning projects, and growing in leadership and responsibility within the company. I truly deserved it. I wrote a 1-pager with all of my accomplishments over the past year, the additional duties I was performing, and the average market salary from multiple sources. I provided all the evidence and data to support a salary increase. I made it easy to say yes.
Then, I moved to a different company as a Senior Risk Analyst because I knew it’s what I had to do to continue to grow my skills. I had several competing offers for higher salaries which showed me my true worth and allowed me to negotiate a higher salary at my chosen company (+37%). I let the market decide my salary through multiple offers instead of guessing random numbers in interviews. I used my other offers as leverage to get more money!
In my most recent job switch 2.5+ years ago, I was seeking a new growth opportunity and increased my salary by 18%. I attribute my success in this switch to working really hard on my interviewing and communication skills. I focused on how to communicate my value through the STAR method, live coding, and statistics.
This puts me at a ~110% increase from $73K to $153K in only 11 months… I got an internal raise by self-advocating for myself with a 1-pager and then job hopped twice. I had a busy year, OK 😅 It’s not ideal to job hop twice in 1 year, but my senior risk analyst job ended up being not what I wanted and a terrible fit, so I left in 4 months. But hey, I did get another salary increase!!
Here are my biggest salary takeaways:
ALWAYS negotiate your salary (Notice how my salary grew when I started negotiating!)
Be on top of the market value— know your worth and talk to others in your field.
Don’t lowball yourself— let the market decide your value.
Practice interviewing— show your value through communication and tech interviews.
Be transparent with others— you never know who you might help!
This was inspired by a few conversations I’ve had recently with entry-level analysts who were bummed to get offers lower than expected. I shared my salary trajectory with them and reassured them that they could increase their salary quickly after getting some valuable experience. It really helped motivate them to see the upward potential in this field, and I think they felt better knowing that a 6 figure Data Analytics salary isn’t realistic for your first role.
Being transparent can only help others.
What’s your salary? 👀
If you’re starting from scratch to become a data analyst, consider my BDE Bundle🔗 [ https://substack.com/redirect/f17ffa37-9cd7-418a-bc42-81fdf5a14fdf?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ] program which provides technical upskilling paired with maximum support, resources, and guidance from me on your job search (BIG Black Friday Sale coming!). You’ll get my beginner SQL course, intermediate SQL course, portfolio projects and instructions, interview prep, and access to the Discord and monthly events. You’ll also get personal reviews on your resume, LinkedIn profile, and portfolio from me!
It’s the fastest, easiest, and least painful way to land your first data analyst job! Check out everything it includes to support your success below:
That’s a wrap on our data cleaning! Don’t forget to add your name to the Black Friday waitlist to make sure you get first access to all the deals when they drop! Spots are limited, so if you’re not sure, just get on the list just in case!
Bye BDEs 💅🏼
Jess Ramos 💕

I’m Jess Ramos, the founder of Big Data Energy and the creator of the BEST SQL course and community: Big SQL Energy⚡️. Hi Candace, it’s time for lesson 2!

 

Today I want to take things up a gear and tell you the 6 skills you need to be a great life coach. ( https://pages.jayshettycoaching.com/jscs-pathway-day-2-funnel/?el=day-2-email-2-pathway-funnel&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+VSL%2FPathway+Funnel&utm_content_name=D2E2+Pathway&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io )

You probably already have some of these skills…

But you may not realize how naturally gifted you are for life coaching.

Of course, you’ll need some help to polish them before you can become a professional life coach…

But that’s where my team and I can help.

Click here and watch this video where I explain the 6 skills you need. ( https://pages.jayshettycoaching.com/jscs-pathway-day-2-funnel/?el=day-2-email-2-pathway-funnel&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+VSL%2FPathway+Funnel&utm_content_name=D2E2+Pathway&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io )

 

 

Prefer to read?

No problem— click here to download today’s lesson book. ( https://drive.google.com/file/d/1oKBVf4JkmWQDWxzyrmLgCyNg_ZM6_iHp/view?usp=sharing/?el=day-2-email-2-pathway-funnel&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+VSL%2FPathway+Funnel&utm_content_name=D2E2+Pathway&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io )

 

 

And…

If you’re interested in learning more about what it takes to become a life coach…

Then check out this free workshop. ( https://pages.jayshettycoaching.com/ovsl-video-f/?el=day-2-email-2-footer-funnel-OVSL&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+VSL%2FPathway+Funnel&utm_content_name=D2E2+Pathway&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io )

In it, I talk all about the easy, ABC Coaching Framework I developed and use to coach my own clients.

Whether I’m helping a couple overcome issues in their marriage…

A high-level executive tackle their imposter syndrome…

Or helping restore confidence in a pro-athlete.

The ABC Coaching Framework is the foundation of what I do and what I teach the students inside my life coaching school.

You won't learn about this anywhere else. ( https://pages.jayshettycoaching.com/ovsl-video-f/?el=day-2-email-2-footer-funnel-OVSL&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+VSL%2FPathway+Funnel&utm_content_name=D2E2+Pathway&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io )

In the next lesson, we’re going to move to the next step in a life coach’s career— finding your ideal clients.

So, make sure you check your inbox again at 4pm time tomorrow for Lesson 3.

Hope you enjoy today’s lesson!

p$ Salesforce Discovers AI Agents Exist, Names It Like a 90s Action Movie

   product name. Now with Slack integration, so your AI can ghost you in real-time.

   still waiting for their ChatGPT licenses to pay off. (source)

p'bp; Meta Yoinks Another Founder with Monopoly Money

 * Andrew Tulloch just ditched Mira Murati's startup to rejoin Meta's "Superintelligence Lab" (yes, they actually call it that).
   The compensation package was reportedly "stupid money."

 * Why it matters: Meta's strategy is simple - if you can't innovate, just buy everyone who can. Zuck's collecting AI researchers
   like PokC)mon cards. (source)
   [https://www.wsj.com/tech/ai/thinking-machines-lab-co-founder-departs-for-meta-442d7461?utm_source=galaxy.ai&utm_medium=newsletter]




p TSMC Makes 28% More Money, Still Can't Ship Chips Fast Enough

 * Taiwan's chip monopoly posted record profits because everyone needs GPUs to train models that argue on Reddit. Samsung's also
   swimming in cash from memory chip sales.

 * Why it matters: The real AI winners aren't the model builders - it's the hardware dealers selling $40K shovels in this gold
   rush. (source)
   [https://www.reuters.com/world/china/tsmc-q3-profit-expected-soar-28-ai-spending-boom-2025-10-13/?utm_source=galaxy.ai&utm_medium=newsletter]




p Someone Just Bet $5 Billion That AI Data Centers Won't Melt the Grid

 * Brookfield is dropping $5B on Bloom Energy's fuel cells to power AI data centers. Because apparently nobody thought about where
   the electricity would come from.

 * Why it matters: Turns out training GPT-5 requires more power than a small country. We're literally building power plants just
   to generate memes faster. (source)
   [https://www.reuters.com/business/energy/brookfield-bloom-energy-launch-up-5-billion-ai-infrastructure-partnership-2025-10-13/?utm_source=galaxy.ai&utm_medium=newsletter]




p&p* Cerebras Wants to Build Nvidia Alternatives in the Desert

 * The AI chip startup is setting up shop in the UAE for the "Stargate" project (not the sci-fi one). They're doubling their data
   centers and filing for IPO.

 * Why it matters: The UAE is speedrunning the tech hub playbook - skip the garage startups, go straight to billion-dollar AI
   infrastructure. (source)
   [https://www.reuters.com/world/middle-east/cerebras-aims-deploy-ai-infrastructure-massive-stargate-uae-data-centre-hub-2025-10-13/?utm_source=galaxy.ai&utm_medium=newsletter]




p. Elon Promises AI-Generated AAA Game by 2025 (Sure, Jan)

 * xAI hired Nvidia's world-model experts to build entire video games with AI. Musk says playable by end of 2025. The Cybertruck
   was also supposed to be bulletproof.

 * Why it matters: If this works, game devs are cooked. If it doesn't, we'll add it to the list of Elon deadlines that aged like
   milk. (source) [https://www.ft.com/content/ac566346-53dd-4490-8d4c-5269906c64ee?utm_source=galaxy.ai&utm_medium=newsletter]




p< London Finance Jobs Up 9% (All AI-Related, Obviously)

 * Financial firms are panic-hiring anyone who can spell "LLM" as they rush to "commercialize AI platforms" (translation: figure
   out what to do with ChatGPT).

 * Why it matters: AI is creating jobs... for people who will eventually automate everyone else's jobs. Circle of life. (source)
   [https://www.reuters.com/business/world-at-work/fintech-ai-drive-london-finance-job-vacancy-growth-q3-recruiter-says-2025-10-13/?utm_source=galaxy.ai&utm_medium=newsletter]




p* Palmer Luckey Built Iron Man's Helmet for Real Soldiers

 * Anduril's "EagleEye" puts AR displays in military helmets with AI assistance. It's like Call of Duty HUD but people actually
   die.

 * Why it matters: Luckey went from selling Oculus to Facebook to literally augmenting warfare. Character arc of the century.
   (source)

Wow…

 

According to a new survey, as much as 50% of Americans want to completely change their career in 2024.

 

That’s over 80 MILLION people who want to quit their frustrating, stressful old job…

 

And discover something that gives them more fulfillment, more income, more free time.

 

Are you one of them, Candace?

 

Because if so…

 

I have 3 questions that could tell you if a career in COACHING is just the new career change you need this year.

 

Ready?

 

* Are you a keen listener, who loves working with people and genuinely wants to serve others?
* Have you always looked up to coaches, leaders, thinkers and other people who inspire through their wisdom?
* Are you keen to learn and invest in your growth this year and beyond?
If you answered YES to all 3 of those questions.

 

Congratulations!

 

I want to invite you to be mentored by me and my team.

 

We’ll take you step-by-step through everything you need to know to become a certified coach.

 

(Even if you’ve never coached before).

 

So in JUST 5 months time…

 

You could begin to shift away from your tiresome 9 - 5…

 

And start a rewarding new career as a professional, certified coach.

 

With a new potential source of income from helping others achieve their goals for their life, career, and relationships…

 

While you work as many hours as you want, with clients you choose, and from anywhere in the world.

 

How does that sound to you?

 
 

Well, we get very involved in mentoring our students, so we can’t accept everyone who applies.

 

But I’m confident you could be a great fit.

 

That’s why I want to offer you 1 of the final places in the next cohort of my coaching school.

 

Just fill in this form to apply to become a Jay Shetty certified coach ( https://call.jayshettycoaching.com/?el=day-5-email-1-funnel-booking&utm_campaign=booking-funnel&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+VSL%2FPathway+Funnel&utm_content_name=D5E1+VSL+V2&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io ).

 

(It’s just a few basic questions)

 

And if you’re successful…

 

You can start being mentored by me and my team RIGHT AWAY…

 

And be bursting with wisdom, confidence and ready to start your new career as a certified coach.

 

Just follow the steps from this page onwards:

 

Click here and apply to become a Jay Shetty certified coach. ( https://call.jayshettycoaching.com/?el=day-5-email-1-funnel-booking&utm_campaign=booking-funnel&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+VSL%2FPathway+Funnel&utm_content_name=D5E1+VSL+V2&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io )

Dear friends,

I’m thrilled to announce my latest course: Agentic AI! This course will get you up to speed building cutting-edge agentic workflows. It is available from DeepLearning.AI here (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VX2Hy18jjGDLW4_q9t73nS1nyW1-ywb15DpJtWN5SJSmj3prCCW7lCdLW6lZ3l-W4kBklg4jgyWxW6zSxgx97fSVvW2d9p7T7GTyJnW16vq0S1Kr9QfW923bdy1yM66ZVYkBJj4QYmkqW9dH4Yh7Wlhh1N3pGv59LMnpCW80RbvY7YB2QjN6mTQpMqPcZKW8YnGKC9b1MvcW6HTGlZ1t-rZVW6sYpwt8k3JKKW55cNNn1lMdZGW8YV3CV7G0ttvW2VTTg-8BrwH7W5qcqSP99QLLXW3C_TBg6mBG_lW2yW5DP2cFGGcW4377KH1XYvX6W5BG61K8PsPhQW6zFgLF5vg_6hW7mK9Sg5yqZ1HN8L8CxZJVxWZf2zch2j04 ) . The only prerequisite is familiarity with Python, though knowing a bit about LLMs helps too.

This self-paced course is taught in a vendor-neutral way, using raw Python — without hiding details in a framework. So you’ll learn the core concepts that you can then implement using any popular agentic AI framework, or using no framework.

Specifically, you’ll learn how to implement four key agentic design patterns:

- Reflection, in which an agent examines its own output and figures out how to improve it

- Tool use, in which an LLM-driven application decides which functions to call to carry out web search, access calendars, send email, write code, etc.

- Planning, where you’ll use an LLM to decide how to break down a task into sub-tasks for execution, and

- Multi-agent collaboration, in which you build multiple specialized agents — much like how a company might hire multiple employees — to perform a complex task.

More important, you’ll also learn best practices for building effective agents.

Having worked with many teams on many agents, I’ve found that the single biggest predictor of whether someone can build effectively is whether they know how to drive a disciplined process for evals and error analysis. Teams that don’t know how to do this can spend months tweaking agents with little progress to show for it. I’ve seen teams that spent months tuning prompts, building tools for an agent to use, etc., only to hit a performance ceiling they could not break through.

But if you understand how to put in evals and how to monitor an agent’s actions at each step (traces) to see when part of its workflow is breaking, you’ll be able to efficiently home in on which components to focus on improving. Instead of guessing what to work on, you'll let evals data guide you.

You’ll also learn to take a complex application and systematically decompose it into a sequence of tasks to implement using these design patterns. When you understand this process, you’ll also be better at spotting opportunities to build agents.

The course illustrates these concepts with many examples, such as code generation, customer service agents, and automated marketing workflows. We also build a deep research agent that searches for information, summarizes and synthesizes it, and generates a thoughtful report.

When you complete this course, you’ll understand the key building blocks of agents as well as best practices for assembling and tuning these building blocks. This will put you significantly ahead of the vast majority of teams building agents today.

Please join me in this course (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VX2Hy18jjGDLW4_q9t73nS1nyW1-ywb15DpJtWN5SJSmj3prCCW7lCdLW6lZ3l-W4kBklg4jgyWxW6zSxgx97fSVvW2d9p7T7GTyJnW16vq0S1Kr9QfW923bdy1yM66ZVYkBJj4QYmkqW9dH4Yh7Wlhh1N3pGv59LMnpCW80RbvY7YB2QjN6mTQpMqPcZKW8YnGKC9b1MvcW6HTGlZ1t-rZVW6sYpwt8k3JKKW55cNNn1lMdZGW8YV3CV7G0ttvW2VTTg-8BrwH7W5qcqSP99QLLXW3C_TBg6mBG_lW2yW5DP2cFGGcW4377KH1XYvX6W5BG61K8PsPhQW6zFgLF5vg_6hW7mK9Sg5yqZ1HN8L8CxZJVxWZf2zch2j04 ) , and let’s build some amazing agents!

Keep building,

Andrew

Claude Levels Up

Anthropic updated its mid-size Claude Sonnet model, making it the first member of the Claude family to reach version 4.5. It also enhanced the Claude Code agentic coding tool with long-desired features.

Claude Sonnet 4.5: The new model offers (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VX2Hy18jjGDLW4_q9t73nS1nyW1-ywb15DpJtWN5SJSmj3prCCW7lCdLW6lZ3pQW880K544y72hyW7fcMqb5C4xbYW5PMF-55KQNMVW30k7MZ144K-nW2DJF5k4KKJTtW3Pbs0_3TDfZ4W3jy6313_9WSFW3bcqtk4G6JQ8V1cwJf9cwWKcW6QS6DQ75jVC4W5pNkPf8jHX_ZVdmzKg2DGjbGW7R4klP4R3t74W8ZrNDk8S7_1qW73Wq988Wbfc3W8QSLf77-m0PGN1JQLZJ3mTLmW1DQR5L7mjQX1W3H19Vk6ChYP6W5H01tn54V7jsN2Wsgnl1fShnW7TPTh24cvzp4VXQ9jH7JShlmW1hssl53hnWbkdTN9wl04 ) a substantial increase in performance as well as a variable budget for reasoning tokens.

- Input/output: Text and images in (up to between 200,000 to 1 million tokens depending on service tier), text out (up to 64,000 tokens)
- Availability: Free via Claude.ai (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VX2Hy18jjGDLW4_q9t73nS1nyW1-ywb15DpJtWN5SJSlK3prCCW69sMD-6lZ3nkW2YJPRG4c84WxN5ZTly-DtkLLN7znfvDRFZYkW14sD5t29jmx_W8zhKxQ61K0V0W2583Bp7xcjr4N2QQ-RQ7B7x2W5ztWYp2dSlBWW5knqPS4Lg9N2VcmTSp6FYx1yW4jxVWR5RV1sWN6NDZZjSBJcVW4FxzTK26j7WpW56gSPm119DvBW5GQ0v_83FPTzW4RYgLJ1KF4sbW24xHSs5Yw_m7W6TGYB44-z23bW4m1V1Z2nTm5XW1m0RQc1PWZzNf1kBVR404 ) , API access $3/$15 per million tokens input/output via Anthropic, Amazon Bedrock, and Google Vertex
- Features: Reasoning with variable token budget, extended processing time (“hours” according to the documentation), serial (rather than simultaneous) completion of tasks
- Knowledge cutoff: January 2025
- Undisclosed: Model architecture, training data and methods

Results: In Anthropic’s tests, Claude Sonnet 4.5’s coding metrics stood out, but it performed well on broader assessments, too.

- With a reasoning budget of 32,000 tokens, Claude Sonnet 4.5 currently tops the LM Arena Text Leaderboard (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VX2Hy18jjGDLW4_q9t73nS1nyW1-ywb15DpJtWN5SJSm03prCCW6N1vHY6lZ3q3W7FGqSS8R5bn8W3q25vf27SKNKW8yHBgz81Lp0cVsBNmh6DnY2TW4snDzB6kGnlRW2H2S316sg5kyW8gXbcw8FgsDdW8yxpWP3wPrzYW6xQ-_Y6yCjv_W8kBz3W5Wwj-NW6gg_tY14v5qtW6q5gP26v0SSqW5hp0402ynRwjVlXmb199VHKrW4hjJNr2vbQp7W1YpnF46w4dk_W6jrqFb2RkSMCW6t7dXN3G058-W1_DTYS432kk9W58HFdx40L1c0W7YrP--9hbBjgW7R15VY4-BSXzf5Q7Gx-04 ) . Without reasoning, it ranks fourth.
- On coding challenges in SWE-bench Verified, Claude Sonnet 4.5 (82 percent) raised the state of the art, outperforming previous leaders Claude Sonnet 4 (80.2 percent) and Claude Opus 4.1 (79.4 percent).
- It achieved 61.4 percent on the computer-use benchmark OSWorld (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VX2Hy18jjGDLW4_q9t73nS1nyW1-ywb15DpJtWN5SJSm03prCCW6N1vHY6lZ3ntW527mzd4NhfnNN2X9K7pkHwC7W25gfk31ZycPhW19tYwQ4XSZxbVz-rmy18QhbwVVg_Wf77t_ZyW6ZfHX019DVvzN8f4X5y1zjYlN642FspPWKt3W881yL52Qq-rKW4JXbwp6CP_tVW90Z9r05ZbN-NW3j8DH-6shq3CW7s_s4y1z2x0rV_F1dF7zlwdyW1q_hgL4FY-GPVCVhqM2GwcFWVhdLh78cQSWXMqNqGHQR2CCN2XS5Fmbk3whW79ZnVB3CSVwnV5mLK04WFjdCf7y896804 ) , well ahead of other models in available leaderboards.
- It achieved 100 percent on AIME 2025’s math problems when it used Python tools, although GPT-5 dominated when neither model used tools.
- On tests of visual reasoning such as GPQA-Diamond and MMMLU, Sonnet 4.5 generally outperformed the larger Claude Opus 4.1 but fell short of Google Gemini Pro 4.5 and OpenAI GPT-5.

Claude Code: Anthropic’s agentic coding tool got a design overhaul (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VX2Hy18jjGDLW4_q9t73nS1nyW1-ywb15DpJtWN5SJSmW3prCCW8wLKSR6lZ3n6W3Jx6Gs33b1gVMBJ9wmxS8HHW2m2sfm1yVdmtW6dzg_P3X4X3RW6tBW475r-mkKW1hQSzZ49-Pj6W3zKp6T4Km36ZN5RckTHN_vqgW4rTg362XdMSyW1YK59w2rKW9gW311dKz41krwRW76LJ483NYN-bW2dYk8z7ypP4pN76TVRn7FB3vW2kRVCy97KX7MW25vTFq5vBVbrVTFYCl9kd9JCW604-wS7v3h1xN8swBJwzxjNCW5D0MmT8hnj3PN4tVBbTMtcLlW5nLTqY5KpXsCW36sBSf98SMD-W909VQ94Rdj1KN3nYkvzxJTGnW3mRvnX4jJ9LnW8Xc8gP7qw5-VVwn0mk7t92Fpf85ZjvR04 ) that adds a number of fresh capabilities. Notably, it comes with a software development kit — based on the same software infrastructure, toolkit, orchestration logic, and memory management that underpins Claude Code — for building other agentic tools.

- Claude Agent SDK. The new software development kit (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VX2Hy18jjGDLW4_q9t73nS1nyW1-ywb15DpJtWN5SJSmj3prCCW7lCdLW6lZ3mTW4N2LWZ94n-rDW3jZDlr3Xrq3jW29xHSZ4dqlL9VH3DWT76bS-QW7JBM158vBJgyW2XCNcy1WswS8W6JvrNH2Z-t58W8jtRgz2J_CtdW5hbFQJ6MR6pNW4Rk2G8716DnlW3MS6H26TNSFhW38vMz44K0J2gW29c9Jw63MCyjW9kDK348WTWxLW2pXTF08vsJGgW6WLyVd731BZHW4rsZXp7Tfs4KW6X_mf87HTTvNW6-_37L6-9xp8W6BGS4k3NsHZvV7hFy421MlHQW4vtJ841PnhwQW8Ycrj97YmsdwW2lglmw1p4ZY-f8wyPQz04 ) pairs Claude models with software tools for web search, file management, code deployment, and other autonomous capabilities. It provides building blocks for all of Claude Code’s functionality so you can build your own agentic applications.
- Context tracking. Agentic use cases require continuity even when inputs exceed a model’s input context limit. When a model’s message history approaches this limit, Claude Code asks the model to summarize the most critical details and passes the summary to the model as the latest input. It also removes tool results when they’re no longer needed, making room for further input.
- Memory. A new API “memory tool” enables the model to store and retrieve especially important information like project states outside the input.
- Checkpoints. Claude Code now stores checkpoints, preserving safe states that it can revert to in case of mistakes. It also added an IDE extension that can be used in VSCode and similar applications in lieu of the terminal.

Behind the news: Founded by ex-Open AI employees, Anthropic markets itself as an alternative to that company: safer, more humane, and more tasteful. Although it hasn’t stopped touting those values, the emphases have grown simpler: coding (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VX2Hy18jjGDLW4_q9t73nS1nyW1-ywb15DpJtWN5SJSlq5m_5PW5BWr2F6lZ3lNW1v6DB85bymdNW6Jyzh16-T51dW3Np1FP1lHBB8W5jN-CG1DM9gdW6k7rm31XS0c5W3wWj1G2t_5P3W5Kwkdr5SdwTzMc8ktqGF353W6_J_wk8cFgdqW4VRK192mxtF7W7n8ywZ49wkn7W7LWtHm78tZTKW1tMGyL91g09HW1L1SjS8CnZfWW3_mTHl4bMcGlW57C_VT8NQPlcW5xRS0F95Lb_mW1Jbhc07H_wlHW6DZWZm8y40TWW1JPXng7W5_wyN8M60Xp4Fl7wW3fW1Xt5vXJ4NW619_cD1K0tGSW84r9qW5D84gxW61PQz93JfyVLN4-czt8xsc4qW6-X5mw5BxsqyW250xWh7X7755W4mbSHX6wrJydW5S-7M825FKLFW3shZ2-35ktLbVhyQfF5sCwXCW2MpP5D6fFLkCVcsCqC7lNrMcf4yhg8C04 )  and workplace productivity. While ChatGPT may be synonymous with AI among consumers, Anthropic is focusing on software developers and businesses.

Why it matters: The coupling of Claude Sonnet 4.5 with the enhanced Claude Code reflects Anthropic’s emphasis on workplace productivity. This focus speaks to some of the business world’s anxieties: When will AI pay off for my workforce? When will it transform what they do? For now, coding (via Claude Code or a competitor) is one obvious answer.

We’re thinking: The Claude Agent SDK is a significant release that will enable many developers to build powerful agentic apps. We look forward to an explosion of Claude-based progeny!

OpenAI, Meta Diversify AI Product Lines

OpenAI and Meta, which have been content to offer standalone chatbots or tuck them into existing products, introduced dueling social video networks and other initiatives designed to boost revenue and engagement.

What’s new: OpenAI’s Sora 2 (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VX2Hy18jjGDLW4_q9t73nS1nyW1-ywb15DpJtWN5SJSm03prCCW6N1vHY6lZ3pVW6c7tQ5687BbYW1dTjWd7XCtHPN7RsTb9DD6tDN4cXZQSPK1LgW31htT737v2yVW5NyFxb3ZyTRsN4lqW2LjX7mhW89Z3dB4-hzKpW6qFlT53Fm3XXVFbvjV7t6hpFW4BkyF969lcvPW2NFVP496SGkpW94CK278mx5PJW5rPgbJ7TDQdsN3K-ds1NBjKHW15Sm2n8NVZPWVnLZx-1h6Yk2W2j-mYL27jcKDW2B2g-T8g0X78N65f__c7b6L2W7PLKx94nwVrQW5ww1NK9j8nwGf7NFnJ204 ) is a TikTok-style app that lets users share 10-second clips, while Meta’s Vibes (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VX2Hy18jjGDLW4_q9t73nS1nyW1-ywb15DpJtWN5SJSmC3prCCW7Y8-PT6lZ3lwW5V2J7D9j0XfTN69NRCR3L4D_W62_0l28SCY6hW9d8BrX5wzZySW3TlSbf7GNSSXW72yw0L4CCRg3W19HJ9j8cCBylW5PxwVn4vgCNNVkZVS75-7fYqW1fbRg_8ss83vVyW3cb88j9hjW1FqNZG3QM5dGN76dDybMmbDKW5cCJ6t3yLPswW82r0_Y9fyNDgW5Nztw66TrYJjW6jfPCW8196kQW3YKSyG9dJ26VW7h_0pH5wnlbxW3BFGmC5svMnySPd943xH03W7c78nh1flLYcW7_pgjq5CDBzYW16tdBP29b4fqW8__2n13X_11gW6wyKk07qDlS1d570-j04 ) enables Facebook users to generate new videos or remix existing ones. In addition, OpenAI launched ChatGPT Pulse (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VX2Hy18jjGDLW4_q9t73nS1nyW1-ywb15DpJtWN5SJSmj3prCCW7lCdLW6lZ3l9W2GGm_F124JcXW5-zYj35g49Q2W3tzkFP3ZLTs0W6GJhZ41NRT83W28_-Qj1G6t5jW4p9Mpk7BflvFW94GDTr63s2C7W7GHwrN4Zp2YpW8PJhVP8DdKLSW8mwnPt2315m4W2ds8jF7Bd2VqW99zLZR1tfdbtMymz5zqw17tW63cc5c8rN9kMN2pJPwq5BC8jW3Vmlrr5khP4YW7rmSHW2JGMF8W5w7Qn16gXgj3W6y4TWt7s8vNxW4L8psH50qXL9W707jtb8_6lTYW3bTwvP4vdk-_W6s2LZm7PlZT1V_NdKV1L_KwNf43c3-H04 ) , which creates personal briefings based on recent chats and data from connected apps like calendars, and Instant Checkout (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VX2Hy18jjGDLW4_q9t73nS1nyW1-ywb15DpJtWN5SJSmj3prCCW7lCdLW6lZ3mWW8g1vmb7McD2tVSRjw-2Z7yCTW324njj2wxrmMW8v2rvJ2nkLNHW3H4s5N5GnjbMW18LxWk32Jvv5W1908fS5MsrxCW2VwkDS3PRmh8F4jZHjz6wPNVSNdCx3j9tP0W2_-1J451yrzqW4pZxyd5Zx86QW2YcGfD7Kw3xbW49snkj83HtjZVfrtNk8Cfz2nV9NGqR1tjqKrW3wVjqc5W1Ss8W2w_Npq6xtrFqW1hDGqn7K7wjDW1yv1TG57V7-nVzkY8F62WYpFW51BtYh3KDsXkW2v-kXn5RV4txW75xRyX3RRNZCf37tcH-04 ) , which allows ChatGPT users to shop as they chat.

How it works: The new initiatives take advantage of existing AI capabilities to boost engagement and bring in revenue.

- Sora 2: OpenAI’s social video app, which topped the iOS App Store leaderboard over the weekend, lets users generate a limited number of 10-second, 640x480-pixel clips, while subscribers to ChatGPT Pro ($200 per month) can produce unlimited 20-second, 1920x1080-pixel clips. Users can generate their own likenesses and permit others to do so (as OpenAI CEO Sam Altman did, inspiring his audience to generate clips of him shoplifting GPUs at Target, among other antics). The company tightened restrictions on the use of anime and other characters after rightsholders complained, Altman wrote (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VX2Hy18jjGDLW4_q9t73nS1nyW1-ywb15DpJtWN5SJSmj3prCCW7lCdLW6lZ3k_W3sNdvQ4JLMPnW2KMBMF5HSL2ZN1RbWGM4fqtnW1Qk02q8HXxpQW78GQv77f_DYgW5mMCnz4nb-2yW3Zb1C917D_60W46b6Y98TG33SW7gQXDV6nmvtQN52vMwjKKywtW8rGmZy7HYC_FW5ylFpf7FgMJDV2S23Q1RdW6gW70MjCX95M0bvW2QbYnt41byfdW2gRdC_2gwdlTW13RqSx3C7ZSJW8q2V_g24CYD9W7M13hG7fF3BpW2nfmSB9cgHkWW6S9Wj144VFP-N16xrg_2F8DKW3BJ09t5tSZkzVP0Cby8500fVf8rV6fl04 )  in a blog post.
- Vibes: Meta’s social video feed appears under a free tab in its Meta AI app or on the Vibes web site (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VX2Hy18jjGDLW4_q9t73nS1nyW1-ywb15DpJtWN5SJSm03prCCW6N1vHY6lZ3ntW5_BwNK7V__b-W25K5Qb2vlQkGW3hvNvg3d9GGcW1rH05t4Lv3JjW8gcyW78HhSYRW7Ch678573f0fW2C3NdY3Mj7-FVkj97t66zJPbW1X56nl3LK0LBW65Bxv05bd6ZtW1nR0545CPDJwN4r2-ywtqPM4W59xv3w3N0R7lW6D-hjB8_HHX5VmM_P-4YGp_xW3GZQX53ZdJ5nW2D0Vhd13RL-zW3snWnz8X7ZSqW7ltd861brT28W1DW5MV7PFjWGW22XcS62y7LfyVZDDZD8vLtWnf7MPjBK04 ) . Users can’t put themselves into the action, but they can generate clips based on images they upload or remix existing videos in their feed while adding music and altering visual styles. Generated videos can be posted to Instagram and Facebook.
- ChatGPT Pulse: Pulse is a new kind of personal news-and-productivity service. It tracks users’ chats, emails, and calendar entries and creates cards designed to anticipate users’ concerns and provide related news, reminders, suggestions, and tips. The service is currently limited to subscribers to ChatGPT Pro, but OpenAI says eventually it will be free for all users in some form.
- Instant Checkout: ChatGPT users who request product recommendations can buy suggested items from Etsy and Shopify without leaving the chatbot’s user interface. OpenAI earns fees on sales, a structure akin to affiliate links that generate revenue for product recommendation services like Wirecutter; the company says its commissions will not influence ChatGPT’s suggestions. Purchases made in ChatGPT are processed via the Agentic Commerce Protocol, a partnership between OpenAI and the payment processor Stripe that is similar to Google’s Agent Payments Protocol (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VX2Hy18jjGDLW4_q9t73nS1nyW1-ywb15DpJtWN5SJSnb3prCCW95jsWP6lZ3mqW6RZ6ZF99N6mLM6gC0s2nDcZW7Z3bx93_Zc2ZVjv4j66-TK5YN50YCjsl42zyW1ZbZbs5ndMpgW31hHT_33kkybW2DSjP99lsPXfW2G4h3L31JtpNW16ZTPj2ltwjQW1hbfTl3GCc8CW1FM7Vm465TPvW6T2JGn2lvTqkW1wV3fV6nlGTTN1v0sRB1MDkNW5gXKnH8xdFrVW4_RLzq1qTpLZW2Vs6L81tbltlW3BxXsq1VwdKzW59s3rj84_dPHN1Ff8g5LHKkcW8fCDN_8fNNr1W74FzYF8rq76SW2n7msC6sdV5FW2WdFws7GLS7lN40G8gz7pk8kW1Dsq2w2jNszPW6V-bYp7MGz7PW7mY87L8bMg9DN4_5ZLLFTVLWf2LKlWs04 ) .

Behind the news: For revenue, OpenAI so far has relied on chatbot subscriptions, which account for roughly 80 percent. However, only a tiny fraction of ChatGPT’s 700 million weekly active users subscribe. Tactics such as imposing rate limits persuade some to sign up, but personal productivity, shopping commissions, and advertising offer ways to earn money from the rest.

Why it matters: Products based on generative AI are already well established, but they’re still in their infancy, and an infinite variety of AI-powered consumer products and services remains to be invented. OpenAI’s ChatGPT Pulse is a genuinely fresh idea, using agentic capabilities to deliver timely, personalized information and perspective in any domain. Both OpenAI and Facebook are experimenting with social video, giving users new ways to entertain friends and express themselves. And, of course, melding large language models with digital commerce may come to feel natural as people increasingly turn to chatbots for purchasing advice.

We’re thinking: The financial success of such AI-driven products is bound to have a powerful impact on future directions of AI research and development.

Qwen3 Goes Big (and Smaller)

Alibaba rounded out the Qwen3 family with its biggest large language model to date as well as smaller models that process text, images, video, and/or audio.

What’s new: The closed-weights Qwen3-Max (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VX2Hy18jjGDLW4_q9t73nS1nyW1-ywb15DpJtWN5SJSnb3prCCW95jsWP6lZ3n3VsB2f57TLfcnW4LtSmN5m2LGvW47Rjv776_6DWW86G-_g7_RyB3VDk5y-6y9bbbW4QqNj77YjfVRW98DX132LbC4HW7W4J691R4fRfW4WywPG3JNVTMVRNVhk4vVhd7VTrWgJ2s2Yh7N5kL1G0hS4HSW8HTcD95mY2XWV2w9-v4yTV4KW6RQvlx64HNQxW1gKJ275CSjb3W6Hnrj-73pc8rW6yC3QB59hQHXW49PjvC3dxtQDW2s2-fv8CxGLXW2wXQtD1qCYy_W2Yl0ZS4P0y1CW829MMN8bvkHNW1YpTv57K45X3W6001VX8DnycgVhRy7D70M4PVW2PBrG04Q2PzdW7lzQ8h38wXWhW19Xyc27j28W-W8G4Fbs96f8t3f8lv7BP04 )  gives Alibaba a foothold among the biggest large language models. Qwen3-VL-235B-A22B (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VX2Hy18jjGDLW4_q9t73nS1nyW1-ywb15DpJtWN5SJSnb3prCCW95jsWP6lZ3m7W25SZK853VVhVW3j7-3h6lBf1fW7W4Vfn6HDSGZVv66bz5LKB-NW3vlJMX8SdHlpV6Dfbt4H1KG5W1S44_98HQggDW5pyVZQ2l8t8FW1zs1qm2CFGh4W1hlC_h2s7QpnW3rcz6j1R_P2NW2HS2f77sTPxjW54PMDN5znb1FW50cZWJ9h0VMPW1N3xB078Xjm0W2mp3n_4JZdnxW4WNvXr3c7zPSW8jjh9S9k2hp_W4CGGkT3N2YrcW55QHvb5Prh6pW9bcwJN3tJxF8W43GlCL9lyMwCW5Jj-4h26zsG6W5dhgB6269jRXW5F434x7hj8-wW4G-X5X91nltkVBw3gL2rMKwdW3CjWT41v-hmPW682Kdn9lbZ_kW2fjbXW41RnYmdL1g9v04 ) is an open-weights model that processes text, images, and video at the top of its size class and beyond. Qwen3-Omni (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VX2Hy18jjGDLW4_q9t73nS1nyW1-ywb15DpJtWN5SJSnb3prCCW95jsWP6lZ3nMW5sCYp-6Xty_qW9hVFRh74h9zDW28YPsY12DJzqW4ZSQrH11RZK7W6vnPgK1D3bMcW2WS1Sw6xZSFHW5pL4xv14mGl1W8NK7Lb1mpVSHW8XJ_w13rjQhNN5JmXCJ67K3DW81TPdt4lCzbrW8Rk6BW4t7Y0hN44Lt0ZRxgq4N3jj-RmPR_yrW7j1Y0z41BsjyV1H23M8xhgYxW6GfdYK5pfKMCW82njP94N9bV5W2JBsMx9gTFF0W1BJFbm6cL_-1W4PpLwJ3b2ss5VQ--gw2WNPvsW98XDwh5yxjcnW1y2w2Y8h2Rt4W7K8F8S3pCl3XW3mG_Rk90FWJSW7PG0g62xXYbkW3MhGs-2yYLRqW18z4bW2QFjPBW6k7SWt4wFnTVf2vm62n04 ) , also open-weights, adds audio to the mix with outstanding results.

Qwen3-Max encompasses 1 trillion parameters trained on 36 trillion tokens. It’s available in base and instruction-tuned versions, with a reasoning version to come. Like Alibaba’s other Max models (but unlike most of the Qwen series), its weights are not available.

- Input/output: Text in (up to 262,000 tokens), text out (up to 65,536 tokens)
- Architecture and training: 1 trillion-parameter mixture-of-experts decoder, specific training data and methods undisclosed
- Performance: In Alibaba’s tests, Qwen3-Max generally fell short of Google Gemini 2.5 Pro and OpenAI GPT-5 but outperformed large models from Anthropic, DeepSeek, and xAI. Qwen3-VL-235B-A22B, a vision-language variant of Qwen3-235B-A22B, is designed to drive agentic interactions that require understanding of images and videos. It comes in base, instruction-tuned, and reasoning versions.

- Input/output: Text, images, video in (up to 262,000 tokens, expandable to 1 million tokens), text out (up to 81,920 tokens)
- Architecture and training: Mixture-of-experts decoder (235 billion parameters total, 22 billion active per token), vision encoder, specific training data and methods undisclosed
- Performance: In Alibaba’s tests, Qwen3-VL-235B-A22B outperformed other open-weights models and generally matched the best available models on many image and video benchmarks, with or without reasoning capability. It established new states of the art among both open and closed models for MathVision (math problems), Design2Code (visual coding tests), and several tests of text recognition. It outperformed Gemini 2.5 Pro and OpenAI GPT-5 on tests of agentic capabilities (ScreenSpot Pro, OSWorldG, Android World), document understanding (MMLongBench-Doc, DocVQATest), and 2D/3D spatial awareness (CountBench). It performed second-best only to Gemini Pro 2.5 on the science, technology, and math portions of MMMU-Pro, visual reasoning puzzles in SimpleVQA, and video understanding challenges in VideoMMMU.
- Availability: Free (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VX2Hy18jjGDLW4_q9t73nS1nyW1-ywb15DpJtWN5SJSmC3prCCW7Y8-PT6lZ3nKW60BYC33kjy5CW8FljrB7Sl0KzW1BJsjF6VkxkyW740t1W5pkZNJN6jW_LjtNSJQW4B4kbW41VpSlW63DMy_3ZpRjkW8mBXb13RPTXZW3cWD7D5VQvtYW34Pp2V44Dq9JW8r8BVk5lmPCdW1Y6Tzk2mkmxTVkXWgZ55F85PW7zNv-06GcMv0VnMV7p4Y7FVrW7gf0FW7tpCvYF1SxxhfctMhN460X6Wz57XcW62l8ly6S3DfZW6H233s1ks2X4W8lWqV8414SWLW59yj_p6KTkcGW15zmwf8X0rdLW5TqWQr8n_-TQW5dvnJB4KJJ7PW14xj9K7Mm5hpf3ZYSn-04 )  for commercial and noncommercial uses under Apache 2.0 license, $0.70/$2.80 per 1 million tokens input/output via Alibaba Cloud (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VX2Hy18jjGDLW4_q9t73nS1nyW1-ywb15DpJtWN5SJSl65m_5PW50kH_H6lZ3nnVpRqwq6-pTnzW2bBDPj6mDfgTW4g_1P3860xXVW5N3bX_2pyTS-W5WtNgy23P-kHW7MGTqh6ShghcW7bjfPG5Wy83sW3nb1ff8_b5gWN8v4dgxB4h6rW8YzFym8sgjM3W7qQDvM2rg_l2W7V36T-2_MZgCVfQcBH2d-QX4W747zM73t4Xb9Vd-ZyP4rJLW6W3nFyxN1-VVq5W8pHCzt2-kxPhW2t2Lv37BlPYVW3-PSmX7KSdW6W4j-N4652Z-RDW5-145X5L0Yp5W6t_dPY5qPF4NW2js94f6hpl89W1W5K21887W36VHzLT_6d6Rh3W41ylDj605pqlW5bV3GH6jsZz5W2tFFFx7XnNb5W1FZk_q1lPyxRVsg2X_3NsfcbVVXSf92fCrfkW7dL4jc8BQtGNf6-nxSY04 )

Qwen3-Omni-30B-A3B was pretrained on text, images, video, and audio, so it translates between them directly. It comes in instruction-tuned and reasoning versions as well as a specialized audio/video captioner model.

- Input/output: Text, images, video, or audio in (up to 65,536 tokens), text or spoken-word audio out (up to 16,384 tokens)

- Architecture and training: Mixture-of-experts transformer (30 billion parameters total, 3 billion active per token), specialized experts for multimodal and speech processing, specific training data and methods undisclosed
- Performance: Qwen3-Omni is the best-performing open-weights voice model, outperforming GPT-4o on many tests. Among 36 audio and audio-visual benchmarks, Qwen3-Omni-30B-A3B achieved state-of-the-art results on 22. In tests of mixed media understanding and voice output, its results were competitive with those of Gemini 2.5 Pro, ByteDance Seed-ASR (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VX2Hy18jjGDLW4_q9t73nS1nyW1-ywb15DpJtWN5SJSm03prCCW6N1vHY6lZ3q1W27f_ft50rMDWW2MNd3-4PT2JKV7F0lV4GfvYjVCHJxk9f39gjW7j2Rl36b07fSN6sDcSP4sR4jW1VMzCV8HvnvwN4mT1MCt7S_5W8jCpx27_pnJDN3QkNJNzybFGW4K0QwM2ZlndTW4pnTMk4693hjW92h4nM221Q6mW88T_7p7bb2nGW6s-Kvr7yS4H1W6WDhRq7sxWRBVFdst55Fc5jgW39P0D_7h0cPjW78sfzm1xy4G2W4PD7T74hHyYmW8lRBfr45FnpPW8lVg4z7c7n72f6TFZkT04 ) , and OpenAI GPT-4o Transcribe.

column1: The approach known as LoRA streamlines fine-tuning by training a small adapter that modifies a pretrained model’s weights at inference. Researchers built a model that generates such adapters directly.

What’s new: Rujikorn Charakorn and colleagues at the Tokyo-based startup Sakana AI introduced Text-to-LoRA (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VX2Hy18jjGDLW4_q9t73nS1nyW1-ywb15DpJtWN5SJSm03prCCW6N1vHY6lZ3m5W8xyJ7Z5HMg6KW3N1c5Z53nh6VW83LrYj6GB-wZW5FFVH15lCLSRW7HggS14-khggW3Q6WSn3t6VXhW1rkKW02jMTq5W7z377F6KFnvQW1sKpFW7kTVqgW8BbvVb3MpWcFW3Dz83l80VRpDMF-4GG_6kJdW7d5kXM8CQ10CW8PC4z94QhrLsW6g012k4Ly63DW3_jcd-9bmGvnW8c0C5J1R3WxfW3tTPzH8JZR8QW1xdGSy6nYcY_W7dh3rz157CFMW5zPJG13tS57mW4d56q76wcBs0d7CbSP04 )
column2: a model that produces task-specific LoRA adapters based on natural language descriptions of tasks to be performed by a separate large language model.
a LoRA adapter is trained for a particular task. However
column4: given a description of a task
column5: to generate a suitable adapter for tasks it may not have encountered in its training.

column1: How it works: The authors trained a vanilla neural network
column2: given text that describes a task
column3: to produce a task-specific LoRA adapter for the large language model Mistral-7B-Instruct.

column1: - The authors trained the network on 479 tasks (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VX2Hy18jjGDLW4_q9t73nS1nyW1-ywb15DpJtWN5SJSm03prCCW6N1vHY6lZ3kWW4t5zsc2hj32tW5gfz0J3J24PxW4kJr5L6SHCtZW6rvzxk1jCf9pN22Zsdzkw0XNW4nl08y6mD3V5N4BqSNW-ns9mW8kX59J4rY7T2VlZPW45r6PhKVbSPkp2X7g2jW3MDZBn1w4NqYN6mzcjD1cxTLW65HqLT31jt65W6XXwdB95nygGW8FQJ1Z99pdQfW4LCczm8VsxhJW25mM4h79XvbMW7Tcvlk46Tb0WW3Yz6vS9gcXn_W6KQv1Q18mp2vW5HhKgJ8WNRtrW60PN8W7n_Q3kf3QdjNP04 ) such as answering questions about physics and solving math word problems. Each task consisted of 128 example input-output pairs and a description like this one for solving math word problems: “This task challenges your problem-solving abilities through mathematical reasoning. You must carefully read each scenario and systematically work through the data to compute the final outcome.”

- They generated embeddings of task descriptions by passing them to gte-large-en-v1.5 (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VX2Hy18jjGDLW4_q9t73nS1nyW1-ywb15DpJtWN5SJSm03prCCW6N1vHY6lZ3q6W2x8g2N2S7swYW7zKkQq60f-cPW76qwFw1JZQ2wW23tZFf816W3fW3VNyFB24bg1QW3XKJkL4PBlb1W30r0rw7bm15dW8Hs5_71WRwTrN44_hxGZsQyjVpcJxH8yP_D1W65Tjdt5CqYtTW8wXHQK9651mNN8q7gZbL0n6PN6RTN-Mc8BFqW15WlKL1mPx3cN9lQpNBKjhvMN6kF0G3mGfCNW4v-pls7J97p9VK_5tb8rH2G1W2tq9f835g3dQVDgB_V6v_fyxW94bCmS7BfSbTf7CVNxd04 )
- Given an embedding of a task description and embeddings that specified layers of Mistral-7B-Instruct to adapt
column2: Text-to-LoRA learned to generate a LoRA adapter. Specifically
column3: it learned to minimize the difference between the outputs of the LoRA-adapted Mistral-7B-Instruct and the ground truth outputs.

column1: Results: The authors evaluated Mistral-7B-Instruct with Text-to-LoRA on 10 reasoning benchmarks (such as BoolQ (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VX2Hy18jjGDLW4_q9t73nS1nyW1-ywb15DpJtWN5SJSm03prCCW6N1vHY6lZ3p0W23hkRH6qqkMnW9b_FCN8bPMnJW2XP33c4H6FktW6-Dpdm58BbqrW3Xs2M35PQB2yW9fgrNc8cwqkvW6KGSxS1HW2YbW4vKlcP9l949FW90RfZY6F4G1xW5Tn-yQ2VPpBJW7ZhZlM28rdf9W4D9dDw3l7pMDW4_zQsk1rDZs5W3Nk2mD1yK5w5W2XzHVG1-08SjW5shlHN24v3hqW5G2RW79ltpTzVS9BbH1BJ-brVdFlvp1QQ8XTW6XLC_z7nZcKgW2M7K1F14GnT5N8zPM6tlHGTmf1qV1jn04 )
column3: and WinoGrande (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VX2Hy18jjGDLW4_q9t73nS1nyW1-ywb15DpJtWN5SJSm03prCCW6N1vHY6lZ3lSW3r6w8D2fhkbmW6HSWp01PM-kMW29DbSZ30L4N7N1W0lDnrKrpfN666hHbrtwZYW7G-3gQ8kKR2PW5x3QPD7cZl3tW4gdpwy7pTDfyW7HDc6B1hrVqqW6zRGPj5TJlBCW4tjGlM6MvzZWW5p1smC51M0TqW2Mfb_r7n2RjzN5lPDt6JMzjPW7Tz5011WjxwtW7_TYGR990WcXW2Rbw3w3Z_RhgV227fh89_fVfW7PS-0g2d-lYgW5n59VG1hfB98W6wT9kv4tlg26W1py9NP5LKLq9f782xf204 ) ). They compared the results to Mistral-7B-Instruct (i) with conventional task-specific adapters
column4: (ii) with a single adapter trained on all 479 training tasks simultaneously
column5: (iii) unadapted but with the task description prepended to the prompt
column6: and (iv) unadapted but with a plain prompt.

column2: Mistral-7B-Instruct with Text-to-LoRA achieved 67.7 percent average accuracy. The LLM with the multi-task adapter achieved 66.3 percent. The unadapted LLM with the task description prepended to the prompt achieved 60.6 percent average accuracy
column3: while a plain prompt yielded 55.8 percent.

column2: the authors reported results on 8 tasks (excluding GSM8K and HumanEval). Mistral-7B-Instruct with conventional adapters did best (75.8 percent). The LLM with Text-to-LoRA achieved 73.9 percent average accuracy

column1: Why it matters: The demands placed on a model often change over time
column2: and training new LoRA adapters to match is cumbersome. In effect
column3: Text-to-LoRA compresses a library of LoRA adapters into a parameter-efficient hypernetwork that generalizes to arbitrary tasks. Because it generates them based on text descriptions
column4: different descriptive phrasing can produce different styles of adaptation to emphasize
column8: or other constraints. In this way

column1: We’re thinking: Training LoRA adaptors typically involves a tradeoff between specialization and generalization
column2: and ensembles or mixtures of adapters can improve generalization. This approach offers an efficient
column3: low-cost way to produce LoRA ensembles
column4: which typically are expensive to train and maintain.

column7: Thank you for applying at Pluralsight!
New Cost-Saving Option and Pricing Updates for Serverless Compute
column9:
**

**

****

******

Dear Databricks Customer,

Significant improvements to serverless compute are launching on or before April 30, 2025, and the promotional discounts that have been in place since May 2024 will end on April 30, 2025 (as previously announced):

* *End of limited-time promotion on serverless Jobs, Delta Live Tables and Notebooks:* Since May 2024, we have been offering a 50% limited-time promotion on serverless compute for Jobs and DLT, and a 30% promotion on serverless compute for Notebooks. As communicated in January 2025, these promotions will end on April 30, 2025. Please view the pricing pages for Jobs ( https://www.databricks.com/product/pricing/jobs ) , Delta Live Tables ( https://www.databricks.com/product/pricing/delta-live ) , and Notebooks ( https://www.databricks.com/product/pricing/datascience-ml ) for further details.
* *Improvements to the Photon engine for serverless:* Databricks has significantly improved its Photon engine on serverless compute. *All Jobs/DLT will see a cost reduction of at least 20% and up to 60%*. Serverless Notebooks will see up to 40% cost reduction. These improvements will go into effect on April 30, 2025.
* *Introduction of Standard mode for serverless Jobs and DLT:* We are introducing a new, lower-cost ‘ Standard mode ( https://docs.databricks.com/aws/en/jobs/run-serverless-jobs#select-a-performance-mode ) ’ for serverless Jobs and DLT. Standard mode is fully managed compute by Databricks and is also versionless, receiving updates automatically and without breaking workloads. It offers reduced costs for workloads where a slightly higher launch latency is acceptable, making it suitable for many scheduled workloads. *Standard mode is now in public preview with full production support* , and can be enabled via the preview portal ( https://docs.databricks.com/aws/en/admin/workspace-settings/manage-previews ) in the Databricks workspace.

These changes and improvements *also apply to serverless products billed to the Jobs Serverless SKUs* , such as Materialized Views, Streaming Tables, Lakehouse Monitoring, and Predictive Maintenance. *SQL Serverless and MosaicAI Model Training and Model Serving SKUs are unaffected*.

The following table summarizes the three modes of serverless compute affected by these changes:

Serverless compute mode Typical performance Key benefits *Interactive mode for Notebooks (promo expiring)*
Best serverless experience for data science, fully managed platform for Databricks notebooks < 10 seconds startup, fast scaling

* Less management overhead and comparable cost to running interactive Notebooks on Classic All Purpose clusters ( https://www.databricks.com/product/pricing/datascience-ml )

*Performance-optimized mode for Jobs and DLT (promo expiring)*
Best serverless experience for data engineering, with fast startup and execution for time-sensitive Jobs and DLT pipelines < 1 minute startup, fast scaling

* Less management overhead and reduction in cost for most customers running Jobs on Classic All Purpose clusters ( https://www.databricks.com/product/pricing/datascience-ml )

*Standard mode for Jobs and DLT (NEW)*
Lower cost serverless experience, fully managed platform to run Jobs and DLT 4-6 minutes startup, conservative scaling

* Up to 70% lower cost (through reduced DBUs) than performance-optimized mode
* Comparable to Classic Jobs clusters ( https://www.databricks.com/product/pricing/jobs )
* Best serverless price/performance in market comparison on standardized benchmarks

Please contact your Databricks account team if you have any questions about Databricks pricing or would like more details on our new offerings.

Thank you,
Databricks

# Still Waiting, Still Cheering

Plus, Tamsen Fadal debunks myths about menopause.

———————————————————————————

_**Welcome to Weekly Wisdom.**__ Every Thursday, we send you a thoughtful piece of wisdom designed to help you live a life of purpose. __**If you were forwarded this message, you can sign up to receive the free weekly email **__**[here.](https://news.jayshetty.me/)**__** **_

I’ve been thinking a lot about friendships lately.

The kind that feel light. Easy. Supportive.
As well as the kind that, if we’re honest, sometimes carries unspoken tension.

You know that moment when something amazing happens for you? A promotion, a breakthrough, finding a new partner, and you have friends who don’t say anything? Or if they do, they somehow make it about them? That can really suck the joy out of a beautiful moment for you.

But then there are those friends who cheer you on and insist on celebrating?

Those people are rare.

Real friends celebrate you, even when they’re still waiting for their own moment. They don’t measure your wins against their timelines. They don’t quietly pull back because it isn’t their season yet. They show up wholeheartedly, without hesitation, because your happiness doesn’t threaten theirs.

But I’ve learned this too: sometimes, it’s not about who claps the loudest. It’s about **noticing the ones who clap quietly**, even when they’re hurting. It’s about recognising that life moves in seasons, and we’re not all in bloom at the same time.

The truth is, friendship asks us to practise two things at once:

* Gratitude for the people who celebrate us.


* Compassion for the ones still waiting for their turn.

If you’re winning right now, take a moment to notice who’s in your corner. If you’re still waiting, remind yourself that someone else’s success doesn’t take away from yours. The right opportunities find us when we’re ready.

Real friends clap when you win. And one day, when it’s their turn, you’ll be there. Front row, cheering just as loudly.

Consider this an invitation to reflect on the people who show up for you, and how you show up for them.

## Supporting Women Through the Shift

One of the more challenging ways to show up for others is by supporting them through shifts and changes in their health. Understanding is key. On this week’s podcast, I spoke to Emmy-award winning journalist and bestselling author Tamsen Fadal about a topic that often gets swept under the rug in the health and wellness world: menopause. Tamsen is one of our foremost advocates for women’s health. She has done courageous work in bursting open the taboos that surround menopause, increasing awareness about its effects on women’s emotions, relationships, and careers. 

In our conversation, Tamsen debunks myths about menopause by explaining the science behind the body’s hormonal shifts. As we discuss the often overlooked challenges and symptoms of menopause, Tamsen offers practical solutions for meeting these challenges, from lifestyle changes and stress management to hormone therapy and community support. This conversation is essential to anyone unfamiliar with the scientific basis and the practical implications of menopause, whether or not they have experienced or will experience it themselves. Tamsen’s perspective not only informs but empowers women to see that their best years are not behind them, but ahead of them. 

Listen on [Spotify](https://open.spotify.com/episode/6Ueca7tRRM73o1PwqMbj87?si=paZweIi1Q9-rupO1VgoybA) or [Apple Podcasts](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/tamsen-fadal-you-are-not-going-crazy-your-hormones/id1450994021?i=1000724349669).


----------———————————————————————————

----------
**Community Challenge** (#)

This week, I challenge you to make a plan to reach out to a friend with your support. If they’re up, congratulate them on their success. If they’re down, check in with them. It could be as simple as a text to a friend you see every day or a note on a neighbor’s door. Whatever it is, **I want to hear about it.** **Reply to this email right now and tell me how you can show up for someone this week**. 

Last week, I challenged you to make a list of the small daily rituals and practices that help you feel calm, joyful, and ready for the challenges of the day. Your responses were inspiring. 

Reader Eye wrote, 

“_My tiny ritual is journaling. I’m an author, and giving myself a few moments every day to answer specific questions allows my inner wisdom an opportunity to get some airtime every day. AND it gives me an opportunity to listen… I write “Good things are always happening to me!” and then I list things that happen to me that are good. It sets me in a framework of grace and gratitude._“ — 

Eye, I’m inspired by the connection you’re cultivating with yourself through journaling. I love the idea of giving our inner wisdom “some airtime”! That wisdom is always there, if we’re willing to listen. Journaling is such a great ritual for clearing the airwaves and finding that frequency.

Reader Swati wrote,

“_Sharing a cup of coffee with my close friends or flatmate, and talking about how our day was – this simple connection brings warmth._“ — 

This is a fantastic ritual, Swati. It’s so practical, but this time of simple reflection with others can be unexpectedly grounding. I love that you make it a conscious, daily practice to find that warmth and connection.

**Click to reply and let me know** (mailto:hi@jayshetty.me?subject=Community Challenge Reply&body=Hi Jay! Here is what I’d like to say:)

Are you still ready to uplevel your life this year?

If you struggle with building a sense of community around you…

Candace...

 

Have you ever noticed that people always come to you for advice?

 

They trust you…

 

And you genuinely love to listen.

 

That’s not a coincidence.

 

You have a gift, Candace 🎁

 

Now imagine if you had the tools, techniques, and support to turn your gift into your professional career.

 

So you can serve more people…make an even bigger impact…and maybe even get paid for doing what comes naturally to you.

 

My team and I have helped over 6,000 students & graduates do exactly this.

 

And if you apply before Friday ( https://call.jayshettycoaching.com/?el=booking-email-professional-coach-161-2&utm_campaign=booking-be&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+161-2&utm_content_name=Upgrade+To+Professional+Coach+by+July+%E2%98%80%EF%B8%8F&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io ), we can help you too.

Hey Candace,

There’s a post I stumbled across on Reddit a few months ago that
I absolutely loved (which has, unfortunately, since been deleted)
that I thought I’d share with you today.

It was about this idea called No Zero Days.

A Zero Day is a day where you do absolutely nothing to move
forward - no writing, no exercising, no learning, no progress.

The rule is to make sure we don’t let that happen. Do something
every single day, no matter how small. Even if it’s just one
push-up. One sentence. One minute.

It sounds too simple to work, but it does. Here’s why:

1. Small Actions Crush Procrastination
--------------------------------------

Most of us don’t get stuck because we’re lazy - we get stuck
because we think starting requires motivation.

But when you shrink the action down to something tiny - “just one
rep,” “just one sentence” - it removes the friction. You don’t
need motivation to do something small. And once you start, you
usually do more.

2. Momentum Is More Powerful Than Willpower
-------------------------------------------

Ever noticed how one lazy day often turns into two… then a week?

The same thing happens in reverse.

The more consecutive days you take action, the easier it gets.

Progress isn’t about massive bursts of effort. It’s about staying
in motion.

3. Your Brain Starts to Identify as "The Type of Person Who…"
-------------------------------------------------------------

If you do something daily, even if it’s small, your brain rewires
itself. Instead of thinking:

🚫 “I should exercise more.”

✅ You start to think: “I’m the type of person who exercises every
day.”

This shift in identity makes everything easier.

4. Perfectionism Loses Its Grip on You
--------------------------------------

One of the biggest killers of progress is the belief that if you
can’t do something well, you may as well not do it at all.

No Zero Days destroys that. You stop waiting for the “right
conditions” to work out, write, build your business, or learn
that new skill. You just show up.

The Rule Is Simple:
-------------------

👉 Didn’t go to the gym? Do one squat before bed.

👉 Didn’t write your novel? Write one sentence.

👉 Didn’t work on your side hustle? Open the doc and write down
one idea.

Even if all you do today is the bare minimum, you’ve still moved
forward. You’ve still taken action.

And that’s what separates people who succeed from people who
don’t.

Try it today. Even if it’s something ridiculously small. Just
make sure today isn’t a zero.

Because tiny actions, repeated daily, change everything.

Have a great week!

Ali xx

column7: Is your intuition smarter than your spreadsheets? (Mine was)
column9:
Hey friends,

You might’ve noticed (actually tbh you probably haven’t lol) that
I haven’t sent an issue of this newsletter in a few weeks. In
August I was visiting London with Izzy and our baby, and decided
to take a break from “content stuff” to be able to hang with
family and friends without the “pressure” of production
schedules. It felt great. We’re back in Hong Kong now, and so I’m
ramping up back into the work stuff, while also enjoying how
baby’s growing up and becoming much more interactive and fun
compared to when she was a potato-like creature who didn’t do
much other than cry and poop and sleep. Now she smiles reliably
(super cute), and actually seems to enjoy being taken for walks,
but seems to need more and more mental stimulation or she gets
restless.

Couple of quick things before we continue:

* Firstly, very exciting news because we’re officially launching
our next app Momentum: Energising Habits (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/92u972n8rdtnh6dqvq8tzuzpl8333hwhz0g26/l2heh6ul3n36vlhg/aHR0cHM6Ly9nby5zcGFya2xlLnNvL21vbWVudHVtL2xpZmVub3Rlcy9pbnR1aXRpb24=
) this week 🥳 The app is focussed on helping you stay consistent
with your habits and leverage the power of accountability to make
meaningful progress on your goals. We’ll be officially announcing
it tomorrow but you can access it early here (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/92u972n8rdtnh6dqvq8tzuzpl8333hwhz0g26/l2heh6ul3n36vlhg/aHR0cHM6Ly9nby5zcGFya2xlLnNvL21vbWVudHVtL2xpZmVub3Rlcy9pbnR1aXRpb24=
) - check it out and let me know what you think 🙏
* Secondly, we’ll be hosting our usual quarterly reset workshop
on Saturday 20th September. This is a great opportunity to review
the last 90 days but, more importantly, set yourself up for
success for the final 100 days of the year. It’s a free event -
you can register by just clicking here (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/92u972n8rdtnh6dqvq8tzuzpl8333hwhz0g26/3ohqz2pesdu3727494ap/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL2F1dHVtbi1yZXNldC0yMDI1LXdvcmtzaG9wLWNvbmZpcm1hdGlvbg==
).

Anyway, this week I wanted to share a reflection prompt I came
across from a business mentor.

I’ll describe the prompt as it relates to business, but you can
substitute for anything else in your life.

Think about how you FEEL about your business, on a scale of 0 to
10. Zero is “this is the worst feeling in the world, it’s going
terribly”, and 10 is “I feel amazing about my business, it can’t
possibly be any better”. Got a number in mind? Okay good. Now
imagine that number increases by 1. So if, for example, you were
a 5/10, imagine that in a hypothetical future, you feel 6/10 good
about it. In that 6/10 world, what does your business look like?
Don’t think too hard about this - just based on your gut
intuition, what’s happening in the business to make it feel 6/10?
Okay great, now add 1 more. So let’s imagine it’s a 7/10 in terms
of how you feel about it. Again, just based on your gut
intuition, what’s happening in the business to make you feel this
way about it?
My mentor guided me through the exercise - in my case, I’d chosen
6/10 as my original feeling. I was surprised to find that I
easily, and immediately, knew EXACTLY what would be different if
I felt 7/10 good about it, and if I felt 8/10 good about it.
Without any “thinking” that went into that, I intuitively knew
what it would look like. I said as much.

Okay great, now what you envision when we take your current
feeling and +2 to it, that’s going to form the exact vision we’re
going to work towards.
This is a… different… way of coming up with business goals than
I’ve ever tried before. Sure, I’ve done visualisation type
exercises where you project forward 3 years, and think about what
would be cool to have accomplished etc. And I’ve done loads of
journaling prompts based around: “What would the business look
like if I didn’t care about money” or “What would the business
look like if I could only get customers through referrals” and
stuff like that.

But this was the first time I’ve done something that was so
clearly “just” about “intuitive feeling” rather than
thinking-based exploring. And I was pleasantly surprised by how
clear my responses were.

The details are a little too “inside baseball” to share, but one
major theme that came up was how keen I am to have a physical
office for me and the Hong Kong-based team to work from. On
paper, this doesn’t make much sense - we could easily work from
our apartment (which we do sometimes), or from a co-working space
(which we also do sometimes), and pretty much everything we do
could be done remotely. But… there’s something that feels really
good and vibey about having an in-person office setup. We had
something similar back in 2021/2022 and it was super fun -
expensive, but super fun. And we had something sort-of similar in
2023 when I rented a massive apartment in Marylebone, London, and
we turned the living room into a co-working space, and converted
one bedroom into a YouTube studio and one into a podcast studio.
Each day we’d have a handful of team members around - those were
great times too.

But even though it was super fun, it always felt hard to justify
the expense. So when we moved to Hong Kong, I was like: “everyone
does this remote thing, how hard can it be, it’s way more
economical to just use our apartment and have team members over
on certain days”. But… now with a baby in the mix, the “hey our
house has an open door policy, anyone rock up whenever you want”
doesn’t feel right anymore. So I’ve been thinking: “hmm should we
get a proper office” but been held back by “ah but it’s so
expensive, I can’t justify the ROI”.

At least not on paper. But… after doing the “intuitive feeling”
thing, I realised: “screw the ROI. I’d feel much better about
running this business if we had a nice vibey office and me and
the team worked from there in-person, rather than our current
remote work-from-home setup”. And as I’ve been writing about for
years, when you feel good about what you’re doing, you become
more productive… so even though the ROI isn’t clear right now,
I’m sure it’ll become clear over time. Or maybe that’s just a
cope, and maybe I just want to hang out with people in person
because it’s more fun, which is itself also fine.

So yeah, we’re now actively looking for office spaces in Hong
Kong. The prices are… eye-watering, as you’d expect in HK. But I
keep coming back to this idea that sometimes the “right” decision
isn’t the one that makes sense on a spreadsheet. Sometimes it’s
the one that makes you go “yeah, this feels good.”

The various insights prompted by the “+2 feeling” prompt have
made me think about how I make decisions more broadly. I love to
pretend I’m this rational creature who makes choices based on
data and logic. I’ll often create elaborate pros and cons lists,
build financial models, ask for advice from 17+ people. But then,
often, I just end up doing what I wanted to do anyway - what felt
right from the beginning.

I wonder if I’d save myself a lot of time and mental energy if I
just… trusted that feeling more? Not in a “yolo blow the money on
vibes” way, but in a “my intuition is also a form of data” way. I
read somewhere that your gut feeling is essentially your brain
processing years of experience and pattern recognition at a speed
your conscious mind can’t match… which sounds plausible.

The tricky part is distinguishing between “this feels right
because it aligns with my values and vision” versus “this feels
right because it’s comfortable and I’m avoiding something scary.”
So I’m not sure how seriously to take the “feelings”…

Anyway, I’m curious – if you did this exercise with something in
your life (doesn’t have to be business – could be your health,
relationships, creative projects, whatever), what would come up?
What would take you from wherever you are now to +2 on that
feeling scale? And more importantly, what’s stopping you from
just… doing that thing?

I’d love if you could hit reply and let me know :)

Have a great week!

Ali xx

P.S. If you’re in / familiar with Hong Kong, and know of any cool
office spaces that might work for a team of 6-8 people, let me
know! Ideally somewhere with good natural light and space for a
filming setup. Also ideally not so expensive that Angus our
general manager has a stroke.

column9:
Hey! Dickie here.

And that "beginner writer" I talk about in the subject line?

Yup, that’s me.

Today, I want to share my journey from being stuck in a
soul-sucking corporate job on Wall Street to, 5 years later,
making $5,000,000 selling a digital product on the internet.

And I don’t tell this story to brag.

No, I tell it so you can see that I was once just like you—I
didn’t have a digital product to sell, and I was just trying to
figure things out as I went along.

-----------------------------------------------------------------
Back in early 2020, I started a newsletter—even though I hated
writing in college.
-----------------------------------------------------------------

I’d seen how people who could write got the best projects, were
promoted quicker, and were the most respected at the hedge fund I
worked at.

But my weekly newsletters were only being read by my mom and my
sister—and while their feedback was great, I knew I needed a
faster way to improve my skills.

So, to try and get more eyeballs on my writing, I started
publishing on X (Twitter).

I set myself a challenge:

*******************************************************
Write & publish a Twitter thread every day for 30 days.
*******************************************************

I’d curate my takeaways from all the podcasts I was listening to
every morning before my 9 to 5 on Wall Street.

After all, what did I have to lose?

* Worst-case scenario: I’d clarify my thinking by writing about
my favorite investors, entrepreneurs, and creators.
​
* Best-case scenario: something else would happen to make it
worthwhile (this could’ve been anything, I had no idea what to
expect).

After 27 days, I was seeing almost zero progress:

* Barely any likes
* Hardly any comments
* And a disappointingly low number of shares

I published my 28th thread and went to bed, thinking nothing of
it.

*****************************************************************
Overnight, the thread went viral and I woke up to hundreds of new
followers.
*****************************************************************

Naval Ravikant had retweeted the thread.

And people started sending me DMs, thanking me for pulling
together all the material (which was a break down of the thinking
of Balaji Srinivasan, an entrepreneur and investor I looked up
to).

This blew my mind—and I knew I was onto something with this
30-day challenge idea.

A simple daily writing habit and publishing ideas on the internet
had caught the attention of people I admired so I decided it
would be fun to help other people do this too.

So, one Tuesday evening, I tweeted this:

​

-----------------------------------------------------------------
I only had around 1,000 followers at the time—so I wasn’t sure if
it’d get much traction.
-----------------------------------------------------------------

But after tweeting about this “accountability group” I was
making, all of a sudden 50+ people were paying money to join what
quickly became the 1st cohort of Ship 30 for 30.

And creating this first cohort is how I got put in contact with
my co-founder, Nicolas Cole.

Fast forward 12 months, Ship 30 was doing 7 figures (!) in
revenue.
-----------------------------------------------------------------

Of course, this isn’t to say it was plain sailing all the way.

Cole and I have made a TON of mistakes and learned some hard
lessons over the last 5 years.

As Digital Product Builders, we had to quickly master the 4
pillars we walk through inside Low-Ticket Launchpad (
https://click.convertkit-mail.com/gku5p88dl5iwudd776rurh8gxxv99bm/x0he7vr8b3uep8wrp0fg/aHR0cHM6Ly9zaGlwLnNhbWNhcnQuY29tL3Byb2R1Y3RzL2xvdy10aWNrZXQtbGF1bmNocGFk
).

*****************************************************************
To build and scale Ship 30, I was frantically figuring out these
skills:
*****************************************************************

* Pillar #1: Product Creation. I’d found an idea that seemed to
work, but it would take me months to turn it into a profitable
product that solved my target customer’s problems AND delivered
real outcomes.
​
* Pillar #2: Product Offer & Pricing. It took me months to slowly
increase the price of Ship 30 from $50… to $99… and eventually
$350+. But if I’d know how to build an irresistible product offer
right from the start, I would’ve been able to charge a lot more,
a lot sooner.
​
* Pillar #3: Product Tech Stack. I had no idea how to build a
“digital product engine” that could sell for me on autopilot,
24/7/365. I tested dozens of pieces of software, and only now do
I feel like our engine is humming.
​
* Pillar #4: Product Marketing & Monetization. After years of
experimenting with different content strategies, I’ve finally
figured out how to generate attention, capture it, and then turn
impressions into customers through email and word-of-mouth
marketing.

But the overwhelmingly positive response I got from the first
cohort of Ship 30 for 30 is what convinced me to continue
building myself as a writer online—and perfecting these skills.

Because mastering these Pillars is what helped me make 7 figures
from Ship 30 in the first 12 months and then over $5,000,000
since then.

This is why I am so excited to help YOU become a Digital Product
Builder with Low-Ticket Launchpad.
-----------------------------------------------------------------

This is the exact roadmap I wish I had when I first start writing
online in early 2020.

So, instead of fumbling your way through months (and even years)
of mistakes and hard lessons trying to build a digital product by
yourself, fast track your progress with us.

*************************************************************
And remember: our first time-sensitive bonus expires tonight!
*************************************************************

So if you don’t invest in Low-Ticket Launchpad before midnight
EST, tonight, you’ll lose access to our first bonus: The Viral
Drop Playbook.

​
We’ve used this playbook to attract thousands of subscribers to
our list (and we, to this day, use it every single week!).

Inside this bonus module, we’ll walk you through how to:

* Create the perfect Viral Drop asset (so people will actually
comment on your post)
​
* Write high-converting social media copy to drive massive
engagement
​
* Set up an automated delivery system to deliver the asset
​
* Write a simple email flow to nurture your new subscriber & land
sales (all on autopilot)

If you’ve been struggling to grow your email list organically
(and sell more products), this is the fastest, most
cost-effective growth strategy we’ve ever developed.

But if you don’t purchase before midnight EST tonight, you’ll
lose access to it… forever!

-----------------------------------------------------------------
​Click here to get Low-Ticket Launchpad (and claim your bonuses
before it’s too late!). (
https://click.convertkit-mail.com/gku5p88dl5iwudd776rurh8gxxv99bm/x0he7vr8b3uep8wrp0fg/aHR0cHM6Ly9zaGlwLnNhbWNhcnQuY29tL3Byb2R1Y3RzL2xvdy10aWNrZXQtbGF1bmNocGFk

-----------------------------------------------------------------

See you on the inside!

—Dickie

PS… Worried this is another “all fluff, no action” course?

Well, I can tell you, I’m ALLERGIC to those kind of courses.

(Yup, I’ve wasted hundreds—if not thousands of dollars on them,

So that’s why I create digital products packed with video

This is everything you need to build your own $350 digital
